-- Colombia Stocks: Grupo Aval, Petrominerales, Pacific Rubiales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-07-17T20:47:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/colombia-stocks-cementos-argos-petrominerales-canacol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.6 percent to 13,653.13, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.3 percent to 1,660.46.  Financial industry companies advanced as  Colombia ’s
 outstanding credit  expanded 18.3 percent in May from a year
earlier, according to government data.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (PFAVAL CB), Colombia’s
biggest banking group by assets, rose 2.2 percent to 1,180
pesos.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)  , Colombia’s largest bank by
market capitalization, gained 0.9 percent to 27,760 pesos.  Oil producers gained as crude rose to a seven-week high in
 New York .  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates the
country’s largest oil field, gained 0.8 percent to 40,620 pesos.
 Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates fields in Colombia, rose 0.6 percent to 795 pesos.
 Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  , a Calgary-based oil company that
operates in the Andean region, rose 0.7 percent to 17,420 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in Bogota at 
